officialTitle: Plan B® 1.5 Emergency Contraception Actual Use Study in Adolescents
summary: This is a non-comparative case series study to assess the ability of females 11-16 years of age, inclusive, who are requesting emergency contraception (EC) to use the study product, DR-104 (Plan B® 1.5), appropriately and safely without provider counseling.

primaryOutcome.measure: Percentage of Participants Who Appropriately Self-selected DR-104 (Plan B® 1.5) When Dispensed Under Simulated Over-the-counter (OTC) Conditions
